{
  "title": "When AI Mistakes a Cat for a Cactus",
  "text": "The article humorously describes how a new AI visual classifier confused a fluffy cat with a cactus. The AI, trying to be helpful, suggested the cat needed a watering schedule and a prickly makeover. The cat’s owner posted pictures of the cat sitting among real cacti, and the internet erupted in jokes about \"prickly purrs\" and \"spiky whiskers\". The piece ends with a reflection on the importance of better training data for visual AI models."
}
